&lt;p&gt;Everlaw is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Data Analyst&lt;/strong&gt; who transforms raw data into the actionable insights our leadership needs to steer the company forward. Everlaw is at the forefront of legal technology, dealing with massive, complex datasets to help legal teams uncover the truth in high-stakes litigation. Data is absolutely critical in helping our company navigate complex use cases, sophisticated user workflows, and the operational challenges of a high-growth, AI native SaaS business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll collaborate with Senior Data Scientists, Product Managers, GTM leadership, Software Engineers, and many other partners to dive into our data ecosystem and monitor product performance, track user engagement, and identify trends that inform our company’s strategic roadmap. You will be responsible for ensuring our data remains a &quot;source of truth&quot; by maintaining rigorous quality standards and building intuitive dashboards that democratize information across the company. As a team, we highly value innate curiosity, an eye for detail, and a preference for solving problems collaboratively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Everlaw, engineering is key to our mission. Our company culture is open and vibrant and we’re committed to the professional growth of our team members, offering an annual learning and development stipend and regular check-ins with managers regarding career goals. If you’re looking for a place that values passion, integrity, thinking big, and a desire to learn, we’d love to hear from you! Think you’re missing some of the skills and are hesitant to apply? We do not believe in the ‘perfect’ candidate and encourage you to apply if you feel you can bring value to our team.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time, exempt position located onsite (3 days/week in office) in Oakland, California.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Getting started&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We want you to feel like part of the team early on! Our onboarding process will integrate you into the company with informative sessions on our product, policies, processes, and team structure and goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We’re excited for you to learn, grow, and contribute right away! We trust that you’ll bring industry experience and knowledge that will uplift and uplevel the team, but we don’t expect you to know everything on Day 1.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;In your role, you&#39;ll...&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarize yourself with our technologies, workflows, and codebase through extensive training and product certification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Transform large datasets into actionable metrics and attributes using SQL and Spark.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explore and develop the right repeatable methods for mining insight from large unstructured datasets, leveraging a variety of tools spanning Jupyter notebooks, Looker, and Heap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and surface metrics that are faithful and precise, while helping the business understand how to drive those metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build out the data context layer (schemas, metric definitions, institutional knowledge, etc.) to power agentic analytics workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise business teams on how to implement scalable, robust telemetry and analytics tracking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About you&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Bachelor’s degree in a quantitative field such as Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Economics, or a related technical discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Up to 4 years of experience (including internships) turning large datasets into actionable business insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience and proficiency wrangling data using SQL.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience and proficiency in applying scientific programming languages (Python, R, Julia, etc.) to data analysis problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of the fundamentals of relational databases and data modeling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;

&lt;div class=&quot;section page-centered&quot; data-qa=&quot;job-description&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Everlaw is seeking a Deal Desk Analyst to join our Go-To-Market (GTM) Strategy &amp;amp; Operations team for a six-month fixed-term during a high-growth period. In this critical “capacity surge” role, you will help eliminate our current quoting backlog and provide expert support for increasingly complex deal structures. As a Deal Desk Analyst, you will act as a strategic bridge between Sales, Customer Success, Finance, and Legal, ensuring your deals are scalable, reliable, and accurately provisioned without creating downstream billing issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will sit within the GTM Strategy &amp;amp; Operations department, specifically focusing on the Quote-to-Cash (Q2C) lifecycle. Your team is dedicated to building the infrastructure and processes that allow Everlaw to scale rapidly while maintaining financial integrity and operational efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a full-time non-exempt position based in our Oakland, California office with a hybrid work schedule: in office M/W/Th with the option to work from home Tu/Fr. The expected length of the engagement would be 6 months.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Getting started&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We want you to feel like part of the team early on! Our onboarding process will integrate you into the company with informative sessions on our product, policies, processes, and team structure and goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We’re excited for you to learn, grow, and contribute right away! We trust that you’ll bring experience and knowledge that will uplift and uplevel the team, but we don’t expect you to know everything on Day 1.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In your role, you&#39;ll...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage end-to-end quoting for new business, renewals, and complex amendments using Salesforce CPQ.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary owner for the Salesforce and ZenDesk queue, managing the intake, triage, and escalation of all Q2C requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reduce wait times and maintain high service standards by resolving tickets within defined SLAs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally with Finance and Legal to navigate non-standard terms and identify system inefficiencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in standardizing deal workflows and systemizing the escalation process within Salesforce to improve transparency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all deals adhere to established price books, discount thresholds, and Everlaw’s financial compliance standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have at least 5 years of experience in Deal Desk, Sales Operations, or Revenue Operations, including hands-on ownership of quoting for new business, renewals, and complex amendments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have advanced proficiency in Salesforce CPQ or a similar quoting tool, and are comfortable configuring products and bundles, applying price rules, and troubleshooting complex quote logic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are experienced in balancing short-term sales velocity with long-term revenue integrity, ensuring deals move quickly while still adhering to pricing, discount, and compliance guardrails.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a clear communicator who can articulate complex commercial concepts to diverse internal stakeholders, tailoring your message for Sales, Customer Success, Finance, Legal, and technical partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a background in SaaS or Legal Tech environments and enjoy working cross-functionally with GTM teams to support scalable, reliable deal structures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are detail-oriented and able to manage high volumes of requests in a fast-paced environment, prioritizing effectively and maintaining high accuracy across your queue.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li

&lt;p&gt;As a Field Enablement Partner, you will be part of the strategic transformation of our field enablement motion from general skill development toward High-Stakes Performance Consulting. In this highly impactful role, your core focus will be enabling the end-to-end sales process and commercial methodology for our emerging segments. You’ll use your egoless communication and work closely with the Product Marketing Team to ensure timely and impactful product launches and GTM strategy. Your focus will be our Public Sector and Corporate Legal segment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Future focus: By harnessing AI-aided performance data, you’ll bypass traditional, broad-based training paths. You’ll deploy precise, surgical coaching interventions that directly drive win rates, deal velocity, and retention.&lt;/p&gt;
